Citation.sTitle: Temperature Dependence of the Thermophysical Properties of 1-Chlorohexane, 1-Iodohexane, 1-Iodoheptane, and 1-Chlorononane at Saturation Condition
Citation.sAbstract: The speed of sound u, density F, and specific heat capacity at constant pressure CP for liquid 1-chlorohexane, 1-iodohexane, 1-iodoheptane, and 1-chlorononane were measured as a function of temperature along the saturation line between (293.15 and 373.15) K. The experimental results were used to calculate various thermophysical properties such as the isobaric thermal expansion coefficient RP, the isentropic compressibility kS, the isothermal compressibility kT, the specific heat capacity at constant volume CV, the ratio of CP to CV, the temperature coefficient of pressure at constant volume (dP/dT)V, and the internal pressure Pi.
